# Super6 copy: no dashes

When **writing or editing** customer facing strings (page copy, headings, bullets, CTAs, meta descriptions, FAQs):

## Do not use

- **Em dashes** (`—`) or **en dashes** (`–`) anywhere in prose.
- **Hyphen as a clause divider** (e.g. `short clause - another clause`). Use a comma, period, colon, or parentheses instead.
- **Stacked hyphen compounds** when plain words work (`weekend long` not `weekend-long`, `in and out` not `in-and-out`) unless it is a fixed legal name or unavoidable technical term.

## Use instead

Short sentences, commas, periods, colons, parentheses, or `and` / `or` to connect ideas.

## Exceptions (do not “clean” unless TK asks)

- **TK frozen blocks** such as the `/ai-events` hero section text defined in `.cursor/rules/ai-events-frozen-top.mdc`.
- **Code**: file paths, URLs, import names, CSS class names, Tailwind arbitrary values.
- **Brand lockups** where a dash is part of supplied artwork or legal naming (ask TK before changing).

## Quick check before shipping copy

Search the edited region for `—`, `–`, and hyphen surrounded by spaces in JSX or template strings; rewrite any hits.
